{"lemma":"وَبَرُ","slug":"وَبَرُ","root":"#.ب.ر","root_slug":"_-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41561","n41562","n41563","n41564"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be rich in hair"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fine hair (specifically from camels and goats, specifically from the hump; used for the cloths and tents of nomads from yore; distinguished from the مَدَر (madar, “loam”) of town buildings)","examples":[{"text":"ثُمَّ يُرْسِلُ اللّٰهُ مَطَرًا لَا يَكُنُّ مِنْهُ بَيْتُ مَدَرٍ وَلَا وَبَرٍ فَيَغْسِلُ الأَرْضَ حَتَّى يَتْرُكَهَا كَالزَّلَفَةِ","english":"Then God will send rain and there will be no brickhouse and no tent and he washes the earth, so that he leaves it blank like a nacre-shell."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"klipdachs, dassie, hyrax, daman (Hyracoidea, of which the rock hyrax Procavia capensis is found in the Arabian peninsula and Greater Syria)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"hairy"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root و ب ر (w b r) denoting a camel with a lot of hair or fur."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41561","headword_ar":"وَبِرَ","root":"wbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabrN","text_ar":"وَبرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"had much"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft"},{"kind":"text","text":"hair]. (S, Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n41562","headword_ar":"وَبْرٌ","root":"wbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", a pl. [or rather a coll. gen. n.] of which the sing. [or n. un.] is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh;) or a masc. n., of which the fem. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, M, Msb, K,) and also a pl. [or coll. gen. n.], (M,) [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hyrax Syriacus;"},{"kind":"text","text":"believed to be the animal called in Hebr."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"שָׁפָן","text_ar":"שָׁפָן","orth_type":"plain"},{"kind":"text","text":";]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain small beast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the cat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the size of the cat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smaller than the cat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the beasts of the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a dust-colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, Mgh, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a hue between dust-colour and white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaHolaA='u","text_ar":"طَحْلَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", this epithet being applied to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waborapN","text_ar":"وَبْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having beautiful eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having eyes bordered with black,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very black eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaHolaA='u","text_ar":"كَحْلَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a small tail,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,) [Golius says, on the authority of Dmr., “ longiore caudâ, ” which is a mistake, for it has no tail,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be of the weasel-kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"very shy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"living in low grounds,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and dwelling in houses"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of its own"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is confined in houses, and is taught; and it is eaten, because it feeds upon leguminous plants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"said to be"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a ruminant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but this is not the case;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and therefore it is said in a trad., that when a man in a state of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iHoraAm","text_ar":"اـِحْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"kills it, he must sacrifice a sheep or goat: (TA:) [a full and correct description of this animal is given in art. “ Shaphan ” of Dr. Kitto's “ Cyclopædia of Biblical Literature: ”] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wibaArN","text_ar":"وِبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wubuwrN","text_ar":"وُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wibaArapN","text_ar":"وِبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibaArapN","text_ar":"اـِبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) with hemzeh in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^asomaHu mino mux~a Alwabori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَسْمَحُ مِنْ مُخَّ الوَبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"The text has missing characters between مُخ and مِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is more liberal than the marrow of the webr"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: because the marrow of the webr comes forth easily. (IAar, T.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^a*am~u mina AlwibaArapi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَذَمُّ مِنَ الوِبَارَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is more dispraised than the webrs"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, T.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alwaboru","text_ar":"الوَبْرُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"One of the days called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aAmu AlEajuwzi","text_ar":"اَيَّامُ العَجُوزِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which are seven, falling at the end of winter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waborN","text_ar":"وَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without the article: for the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sin~N waSin~aburo waA^axay~uhumaA waboro","text_ar":"صِنٌّ وَصِنَّبُرْ وَاَخَيُّهُمَا وَبْرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sinn and Sinnabr and their little brother Webr"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but this may be for the sake of the rhyme. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","T","M","Msb","K","S","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n41563","headword_ar":"وَبَرٌ","root":"wbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Suwf","text_ar":"صُوف"},{"kind":"text","text":", [here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the camel, (Lth, T, S, * M, A, K,) and of the hare or rabbit, and the like; (Lth, T, M, A, K;) and in like manner, that of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sam~uwr","text_ar":"سَمُّور"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or sable], and of the fox, and of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fanak","text_ar":"فَنَك"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or marten]: (T:) or it is to the camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like wool"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Swf","text_ar":"صوف"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the sheep;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so to the hare or rabbit, and the like: (Msb:) originally an inf. n.: (Msb:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awobaArN","text_ar":"اَوْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu Alwabari","text_ar":"اَهْلُ الوَبَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people of the deserts;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the people of the tents;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] because they make their tents of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"of camels [as well as of goat's hair, which is not included in the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabarN","text_ar":"وَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEarN","text_ar":"شَعَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholu Almadari","text_ar":"اَهْلُ المَدَرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"the people of the cities and of the towns and villages. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madarN","text_ar":"مَدَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*a Al$~aYo'a","text_ar":"اَخَذَ الشَّىْءَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biwabarihi","text_ar":"بِوَبَرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took the thing altogether; he took the whole of the thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu bizawobarihi","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ بِزَوْبَرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.)"}],"source_refs":["T","Msb","S"]},{"entry_id":"n41564","headword_ar":"وَبِرٌ","root":"wbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having much"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabar","text_ar":"وَبَر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft hair"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, M, * A, * Msb, K;) and in like manner, a hare or rabbit, and the like; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awobaru","text_ar":"اَوْبَرُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, M, A, K:) fem. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wabirapN","text_ar":"وَبِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, A, Msb, K;) and of the latter,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waboraA='u","text_ar":"وَبْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, A, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","K"]}]}}